Author: yuvadeep
Title: [ANN][ICO][HMD] HOMELEND - A MORTGAGE CROWDFUNDING PLATFORM
Body: Everyone’s dream is to have their own house, and it is one of the basic needs of a human being. Most of the people are not in a situation to afford to buy a home, by taking out a mortgage loan from the bank, only some of them can take a loan for a house to fulfill their dreams.  Homelend's is evolving as a blockchain solution that helps to increase the possibility of housing financing for both the families and individuals.  Peer-to-peer lending is also known as alternative finance where you can lend money to another person. Therefore, without involving banks and other financial in middle, users can easily lend money to others. Homelend's P2P platform works by inserting all the business logic into smart contracts. Homelend's allows all the individuals to borrow money in a clear, trusted and, in a secure and transparent way.  Homelend is a platform where you can collect the total information in a digital way.  Homelends design a lending process that is not only smart but also simple, secure and honest.  It allows the borrowers to apply for a loan and track the details of the application status and helps to directly interact with mortgage lenders. Therefore, Tokens play an important role in allowing fast, user-friendly and smooth workflows that combine and secure transactions.

Body: Hi Pantherx, We are planning to launch our platform in the Asian market where we found there will be fast demand to our solution. Author: warunaferang
Title: [ANN][ICO][HMD] HOMELEND - A MORTGAGE CROWDFUNDING PLATFORM
Body: In Homelend’s platform, the collection of information is performed in an “all digital” way. Even the data residing in paper-based documents must be transferred to a digital repository based on distributed ledger technology. This data is provided by the user and double-checked through professional verification providers. Once the information is verified, a smart contract based on algorithms powered by I & ML automatically performs a creditworthiness assessment of the borrower’s application
